rock’ (Old English <i>hān</i>), the same word as modern English <i>hone</i> ‘whetstone’. Compare   Honer  .","German (<b>Höne</b>), in part of Sorbian origin: see   Hoene   and   Hoehne  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Honer","meanings":["English: occupational name for a sharpener of tools, a grinder or honer, from a derivative of Middle English <i>hone</i> ‘whetstone’ (Old English <i>hān</i> ‘stone’) + <i>-er</i>. In Surrey, Sussex, and Hampshire, the name may also have been topographic for someone who lived by a prominent rock or by a boundary stone, from a Middle English derivative of   Hone   + <i>-er</i>. See   Hone  .","North German (<b>Höner</b>): variant of   Hohner  ."]},{"name":"Hones","meanings":["English: variant of   Hone  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Hone was born in 1416, in Exeter, Devon, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Sir John William Periam. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"1416–":"1416–Surnud","1413–Male":"1413–Surnud","1440–1550":"1440–1550","1416–Female":"1416–Surnud","1413":"1413","1440":"1440","1550":"1550","1416":"1416","Broadclyst, Devon, England":"Broadclyst, Devon, England","Exeter, Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Exeter, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1416–":"1416–Kuollut","1413–Male":"1413–Kuollut","1440–1550":"1440–1550","1416–Female":"1416–Kuollut","1413":"1413","1440":"1440","1550":"1550","1416":"1416","Broadclyst, Devon, England":"Broadclyst, Devon, England","Exeter, Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Exeter, Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1416–":"1416–Décédée","1413–Male":"1413–Décédé","1440–1550":"1440–1550","1416–Female":"1416–Décédée","1413":"1413","1440":"1440","1550":"1550","1416":"1416","Broadclyst, Devon, England":"Broadclyst, Devon, Angleterre","Exeter, Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Exeter, Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Margaret Hone est née en 1416, à Exeter, Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Sir John William Periam. Elle est décédée dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"1416–":"1416–Verstorben","1413–Male":"1413–Verstorben","1440–1550":"1440–1550","1416–Female":"1416–Verstorben","1413":"1413","1440":"1440","1550":"1550","1416":"1416","Broadclyst, Devon, England":"Broadclyst, Devon, England","Exeter, Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Exeter, Devon, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Margaret Hone wurde 1416 in Exeter, Devon, England, United Kingdom geboren. Sie hatte mit Sir John William Periam mindestens 1 Sohn. Sie starb in ihrem Geburtsort."},"ht":{"1416–":"1416–Desede","1413–Male":"1413–Desede","1440–1550":"1440–1550","1416–Female":"1416–De